      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Min-Max scaling squeezes features into a fixed 0–1 range using min and max values, making it highly sensitive to outliers that can distort the scale. Standardization, conversely, centers data at a mean of zero and scales it by the standard deviation, which is generally more robust when outliers are present since it doesn't rely on extreme values. For your dataset, standardization is likely preferable given the outlier risk, though you should verify this by checking for statistical anomalies in your income data.",
